Former finance minister Des Van Rooyen is expected to testify at the State Capture Inquiry. JOHANNESBURG - Former finance minister Des van Rooyen is expected to testify at the state capture inquiry on Tuesday. He will also cross-examine former National Treasury Director-General Lungisa Fuzile. READ: State capture inquiry: Ramaphosa amends regulations The Zondo commission is expected to hear evidence relating to the former minister's appointment in December 2015. Fuzile gave evidence at the inquiry about the impact his appointment had on the Rand and Treasury. Van Rooyen's appointment as finance minister was short-lived. Former President Jacob Zuma removed him from the position after only a fewÂ days, following criticism.